{"id":38850,"date":"2023-02-20T10:37:18","date_gmt":"2023-02-20T06:37:18","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/?p=38850"},"modified":"2023-02-20T10:38:14","modified_gmt":"2023-02-20T06:38:14","slug":"malik-kayfiyyah","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2023\/02\/20\/malik-kayfiyyah\/","title":{"rendered":"Malik on Tawhid: Attributes of Allah are above any modality"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Abdullah ibn Wahb reported: We were with Malik ibn Anas, may Allah have mercy on him, when a man entered and he said, \u201cO Abu Abdullah, \u2018<strong>the Most Merciful rose above the Throne<\/strong>,\u2019 (20:5). How did He rise?\u201d Malik bowed his head in silence until he began to sweat, then he said, \u201cThe Most Merciful rose above the Throne as He described himself, and it was not said &#8216;how&#8217; He did so. A modality is not attributable to Him. You are an evil man and a carrier of heresy. Expel him!\u201d Then, the man was expelled.<\/p>\n<p>Source: al-Asma\u0304&#8217; wal-S\u0323ifa\u0304t lil-Bayhaqi\u0304 866<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <strong><em>Sahih<\/em><\/strong> (authentic) according to Al-Dhahabi<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0639\u064e\u0628\u0652\u062f \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u0650 \u0628\u0652\u0646 \u0648\u064e\u0647\u0652\u0628\u064d \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0643\u064f\u0646\u064e\u0651\u0627 \u0639\u0650\u0646\u0652\u062f\u064e \u0645\u064e\u0627\u0644\u0650\u0643\u0650 \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0623\u064e\u0646\u064e\u0633\u064d \u0631\u062d\u0645\u0647 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647 \u0641\u064e\u062f\u064e\u062e\u064e\u0644\u064e \u0631\u064e\u062c\u064f\u0644\u064c \u0641\u064e\u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u064a\u064e\u0627 \u0623\u064e\u0628\u064e\u0627 \u0639\u064e\u0628\u0652\u062f\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0631\u064e\u0651\u062d\u0652\u0645\u064e\u0646\u064f \u06